<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_security_acl"><sys_security_acl action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><admin_overrides>true</admin_overrides><advanced>true</advanced><condition/><description>SnowCICDTestApp basic users can edit caller</description><name>x_g_nci_snowcicdtestapp_request.caller</name><operation display_value="write">write</operation><script><![CDATA[var sc = new sn_sm.SMConfiguration();
var stateFlowsOff = !sc.isEnabled(current, 'use_sf');
var requestNotClosed = 
	current.state != global.SMConstants.ORDER_CLOSED_COMPLETE &&

sys_update_xml.name: sysevent_in_email_action_76152aa71b44541094edddb6bc4bcbc9
sys_update_xml.payload:
record_actiontrue(new sn_sm.SMConfiguration()).isEnabled("snowcicdtestapp", "inbound_email", false)This inbound email action is triggered when an email is sent to this instance, to a mailbox starting with x_g_nci_snowcicdte or with the subject starting with SnowCICDTestApp and the email is not a reply or forward. This inbound email action can create a new SnowCICDTestApp Request, setting the opened by, caller, short description, description, contact type. The original email will be stored in the work notes. In addition to being able to explicitly set the values of the above fields within the email, the following is done automatically: 1. The caller is set to the the user who sent the email. 2. The email subject is set as the short description. 3. The whole email is added to the work notes. 4. The contact type is set to "email". sys_update_xml.name: sysevent_in_email_action_32152aa71b44541094edddb6bc4bcbcb
sys_update_xml.payload:
record_actiontrue(new sn_sm.SMConfiguration()).isEnabled("snowcicdtestapp", "inbound_email", false)This inbound email action is triggered when an email is forwarded to this instance, to a mailbox starting with x_g_nci_snowcicdte or with the subject starting with SnowCICDTestApp and the email is not a reply or forward. This inbound email action can create a new SnowCICDTestApp Request, setting the opened by, caller, short description, description, contact type. The original email will be stored in the work notes. In addition to being able to explicitly set the values of the above fields within the email, the following is done automatically: 1. The caller is set to the the user who sent the email. 2. The email subject is set as the short description. 3. The whole email is added to the work notes. 4. The contact type is set to "email". Example: This email will create a new SnowCICDTestApp Request for Fred Luddy From: Fred Luddy <fred.luddy@example.com> Subject: FW: SnowCICDTestApp:I need assistance Date: June 11, 2013 1:44:55 PM PDT To: ServiceNow ----- Original Email -------- Please provide me with a ..... -----email.readrecipientsLIKEx_g_nci_snowcicdte@^ORsubjectSTARTSWITHFW: SnowCICDTestApp:^ORsubjectSTARTSWITHSnowCICDTestApp:^EQCreate SnowCICDTestApp Request (Forwarde80falsesysevent_in_email_actionrizknt@nih.gov2020-04-14 16:09:42falseglobal32152aa71b44541094edddb6bc4bcbcb0Create SnowCICDTestApp Request (Forwardee1e42e271b44541094edddb6bc4bcbdefalsee1e42e271b44541094edddb6bc4bcbdesysevent_in_email_action_32152aa71b44541094edddb6bc4bcbcbrizknt@nih.gov2020-04-14 16:09:42x_g_nci_snowcicdtestapp_request
